Three types of ROS—O2
                        ·-, H2O2, and •OH—exhibited similar trends in changing aeration conditions (Fig. 3
                        ). Specifically, during the 12 h anaerobic stage with aeration cessation, ROS concentrations decreased, whereas during the 12 h aerobic stage with continuous aeration, their concentrations increased. This indicates that oxygen is crucial for the formation of sawtooth-like fluctuations in ROS contents (Dai et al., 2022).
